Frontend: All frontend code must be written in React using the Next.js framework.

Styling: All styling must be implemented using Tailwind CSS. Do not write custom CSS files unless absolutely necessary for a specific, unachievable effect with Tailwind.

Backend: The backend server must be built with Node.js and the Express.js framework.

AI Model API: All interactions with the core AI model must use the Google Gemini API, specifically targeting a modern, vision-capable model (e.g., Gemini 2.0 Flash).

Image Processing: All server-side image manipulation (cropping, resizing) must be performed using the Sharp library.

Design Inspiration API: All retrieval of inspirational images must use the official Dribbble API.